review_blob: High bitterness, had what it says, spicy & fruity, not a lot of flavour but has some welcomed freshness after a hot day. The bitterness makes it quick in mouth.
Easily forgetable beer, not much of personnality, light/pale malt. Light bitterness and light lemon Been invaded with foam, quickly drunk.
Very refreshing beer, acid citrus taste, with some bitter aftertaste. fine foam. Id rather drink this at 5C instead of 7C as recommended.
Muddled yellow beer, a helluva foam, not much taste, but smells good nonetheless
33cl Bottle. Average taste (ie not that much taste) , dark,  roasty, cloudy, medium sweetness, full body, sort of creamy. Not very exciting, but nice nonetheless
Fruity beer elderberry/raspberry. Nice for ppl who like it sweet. medium sweetness, light body, sticky, average carbonation,

beer_brewer_name: Brasserie des Sources (formerly: de St. Amand)
review_blob: Classic blonde beer, with a light citrus aftertaste, medium sweetness, light body,
Strong sweet taste which remains in throat, lots of bubbles, full body, sticky, lively, long finish,
Light in the mouth, smells good, refreshing, typical of a beer you want to have on a hot sunny day. Fine bubbles.
